{"key":"processedPost-9884864","value":{"id":9884864,"first":9884298,"last":9919643,"when":1235856991,"utime":"02/28/09 11:36 PM","content":"You can use a salamander type construction heater to heat up a whole storage shed.&nbsp; You could put your manure substrates in trays on shelves, and then heat the entire building up to about 190F and leave it there for 12 to 24 hours.&nbsp; You can pasteurize a few thousand pounds that way.&nbsp; Those heaters run on propane or kerosene and cost about $300.&nbsp; This is how many small commercial mushroom farms do it.&nbsp; You cut a round hole in the side of the storage shed for the output end of the salamander to poke through, while the main part of the unit remains outside.<br />RR","title":"Re: pasteurising large amounts of hpoo?"}}